title: ci: adding release-please
body:
Using the release process from Google's release-please tooling and workflow. Google's release-please opens a release pull request, which automates CHANGELOG generation and version bumps, by parsing git history for Conventional Commit messages. Upon merging the release pull request a new release is created.

* https://github.com/googleapis/release-please
* https://github.com/googleapis/release-please-action

title: feat: converting error handing to anyhow
refactor: merging binary and library
body:
Removing development of the library as it makes the release and development
process more complicated. Additionally, there are no users of the library and
all functionality should be covered by the binary.

title: docs: removing Continuous Integration (CI) badge
body:
As the badge is for the latest workflow not the main branch.

We will also not block a release on checks, so need to run the CI workflow on the main branch. The checks are performed as part of the pull request.
